{"word":"H172 - אׇהֳלִיבָה - ʼOhŏlîybâh - o''-hol-ee-baw' - Aholibah","slug":"H172","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אׇהֳלִיבָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼOhŏlîybâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>o''-hol-ee-baw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Aholibah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05D4;&#x05DC;&#x05D9;&#x05D1;&#x05D4;&#x05BC;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D0;&#x05D4;&#x05DC;&#x05D9;&#x05D1;&#x05D4; - 'oho&#x0306;l&#x0131;&#x0302;yba&#x0302;h  'oho&#x0306;l&#x0131;&#x0302;yba&#x0302;hh</b> - <i>o''-hol-ee-baw', o''-hol-e-baw'</i><p/>(As with <a href=\"#/H170\">H170</a> the first form is in form a feminine of <a href=\"#/H168\">H168</a>, but is in fact for the second form); from <a href=\"#/H168\">H168</a>; <i>my tent</i> (is) <i>in her</i>; <i>Oholibah</i>, a symbolic name for Judah: - Aholibah."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H167\">H167</a>, <a href=\"#/H168\">H168</a>, <a href=\"#/H169\">H169</a>, <a href=\"#/H170\">H170</a>, <a href=\"#/H171\">H171</a>, <a href=\"#/H173\">H173</a>"}]}